A manhunt is underway to find the suspects accused of fatally shooting a pedestrian in Cottonlands on Saturday evening. Residents contacted Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA) to report the shooting.  RUSA spokesperson, Prem Balram, said on arrival the victim’s friend, who had been walking with him, informed the officers that they were returning home after consuming alcohol. “The victim’s friend said an unknown man approached them and shot his friend in the head without warning. The gunman then fled the scene on foot. The victim demised on-scene. The motive for the murder was not immediately established.”